AGI - Flavio Briatore was discharged from the San Raffaele hospital in Milan after a heart surgery for a benign heart tumor. He was the same entrepreneur to tell him in a video posted on Instagram in which he stressed the importance of prevention and thanked doctors and ex-wife, Elisabetta Gregoraci. Britor, who will be 74 on April 12, explained that the tumor was discovered routine controls at San Raffaele, in mid-March. The " benign mass" was removed "with a minimal intervention, using an endoscopic technique", he explained, and the intervention "has perfectly succeeded". "I warmly thank Professor Francesco Maisano, the team of Intensive Cardiosurgery and the legendary Reparto 1 Q of San Raffaele," he added.
&nbsp;
Now it will have to undergo a series of routine controls but chemo or radiotherapy sessions will not be necessary. Then the invitation to do prevention and to undergo controls at least once a year: "I did it two years ago and this benign tumor was not there this year," he explained. "We begin this moment to remind ourselves how futile everything is to health. He returned home," he wrote on social Gregoraci, from which the entrepreneur had separated in 2018.&nbsp;

