AGI - "The Italian government is still. At this point I will ask for a hand at the Quirinale": Roberto Salis, Ilaria's father, in an interview with Republic after Judge Jozsef So's in Budapest denied house arrests to his daughter, stating that "the circumstances have not changed" and "13 months of prison are not so many". Salis also braked on a possible candidacy of the daughter in the European elections ventilated by the Pd: "We didn't consider this hypothesis, we're focused on something else, I have to pull my daughter out of there." "We have resorted, we will redefine the strategy, but it also takes the solidarity of the Italians and a protest against the immobilism of the government," he said, "I will ask again for help to President Mattarella".
The 39-year-old of Monza has been recruited since February 2023 for the accusation of two assaults against militants of extreme right and to be part of a criminal association. He argued that even yesterday the Italian prisoner was transferred with cuffs and chains to the ankles and held by an agent with another chain as a leash. For the father of Salis, "our ministers have not made a good impression, they should do an examination of conscience."
<div </div
&nbsp;
"Nordio said it was our fault that Ilaria was not out of prison, that we lost a year not to ask for domiciles in Hungary," he said in the interview, "now we had proof that it was a phony. And it confirms that the reason why we had not advanced the request of domiciles in Budapest was founded." To the Foreign Minister, Antonio Tajani, who said that "the case should not be politicized". Ilaria's father replied that "there is no politicization or not, this is already a political process." "We feel that the Italian government cannot interfere with the judges of Budapest but the choice to bring my daughter to court in chains does not depend on the judiciary but on the Hungarian Ministry of Justice, in the wake of European norms and the rule of law," he added, "the Italian government can and must make sure that our town is not treated as a dog." How did Ilaria take the no to the domiciles? "It's disappointed, emotionally it's devastating. But the battle is not lost and we will not lose it," said Roberto Salis.&nbsp;
&nbsp;

